Assuming precondition array.length > 0 in the following Java code, explain why the best postcondition for checkArray in the following Java code is to return the index of the largest value in array array:
private int[] array;
public int checkArray() {
     int loc = array.length / 2;
     for (int k = 0; k < array.length; k++) {
          if (array[k] > array[loc]) {
               loc = k;
          }
     }
     return loc;
}
